nted Higher Education for the future. It theoretically expounds on important elements to consider when engaging Higher Education and communities, discussing the nature of the term ‘community’ itself. Special reference is accorded to the difference that lies at the core of these ever-changing communities. It then provides an analysis of an ‘on the ground project’ in University community engagement, before suggesting signposts for further action at the level of policy and provision.This book is relevant to United Nations Sustainable Development Goal 4, Quality education  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEducation, HigherzEurope. 0aHigher education and statezEurope. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  aQuality education.  acommunities.  aglobalisation.  ahigher education.  amigration.  apopular imagination.  aportability of cultures.  apublic good.  asocial difference.  asocial justice.  auniversities.1 aDeem, Rosemary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Budd L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayo, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614093740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526140937423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526140937/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles